name: Cloud Study Jam
description:
Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Google Cloud Console: From writing Cloud Shell commands and deploying your first virtual machine, to running applications on Kubernetes Engine with load balancing, GCP Essentials is a prime introduction to the platform’s features.

Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to complete any labs you want

Agenda:
6:30pm: Welcome Attendees
6:45pm: Introduction to GCP Console
7:00pm: 3 Google Cloud Platform Essentials labs
8:00pm: Break
8:15pm: Hands-on lab resumes
9:00pm: Event ends

Please Note: As this event is a hands-on session, attendees must bring their own laptop and chargers.

Venue: Our team is working on deciding the Venue for this event and will be announced shortly.

name: Google Cloud “Women in Tech” OnBoard - Big Data & Machine Learning
description:
Note:- This event is happening at Google office and requires prior registration on a separate page.

The Cloud OnBoard ML Women in Tech Edition is a free, full-day training event that will provide you with a detailed view of Google Cloud Platform's data processing and machine learning capabilities. Through a combination of instructor-led presentations and demos, you will learn how to leverage the ease, flexibility, and power of data and machine learning tools like Cloud Dataproc, Dataflow, Machine Learning APIs, Tensorflow and BigQuery.

Who should attend this event?

The topics that will be discussed at Cloud OnBoard Big Data and Machine Learning are best-suited for data analysts, data scientists and business analysts.

This event will provide powerful insights if you’re responsible for:

Designing pipelines and architectures for data processing
Creating and maintaining machine learning and statistical models
Querying datasets
Visualizing query results and creating reports

In order to get the most out of this event, you should have:

Basic proficiency with common query language, such as SQL
Experience with data modeling, extract, transform and load activities.
Experience developing applications using a common programming language, such as Python.
Familiarity with machine learning and/or statistics.

See Detailed Agenda at - https://cloudplatformonline.com/2019-OnBoard-ML-WIT-Toronto-Reg.html#agenda

Register at - https://cloudplatformonline.com/2019-OnBoard-ML-WIT-Toronto-Reg.html#register

name: Become a #CloudHero - Online Competition about Google Cloud
description:
Details
### This online event is separate from our Next '19 Extended meetup scheduled on April 27th, 2019. And, you can attend it from the comfort of your home or office or nearby starbucks or in short wherever you have a good internet connection ###

### https://cloudonair.withgoogle.com/events/app-dev/demo - You can pre-register on this page and attend any one of the four 90-minutes sessions ###

What is a Cloud Hero?
Community members from all around the globe will have an opportunity to participate in the Hands-on Labs experience @ Next ‘19. We will participate in one of the Cloud Hero Sessions and play the Cloud Hero game in the same platform, against players at the event.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GFxTCcDW1fw

What does a participant do?
There will be 12 GCP challenges with a time limit of 60 minutes each. During the 90 minutes of the Cloud Hero sessions, players need to play through it as fast as they can to earn points and win the session.

The Cloud Hero lab challenges you to build an end-to-end application deployment experience using multiple GCP services, from GCS to GKE and Cloud Build. By the end of this lab you will have a complete CI/CD pipeline for automatically building and deploying an application on the Google Cloud.

*** UPDATES ***
All Cloud Hero players will have a special badge on Qwiklabs and best players will be recognized globally.

All participants will receive 50 Qwiklabs credits. The first three players to complete the challenge will receive an additional 100 Qwiklabs credits.

All participants will receive their first month free on Google Cloud Platform Training on Coursera.

Please check out the photo, in this meetup event, to get an idea about the structure of the game and time slots which are in PDT Timezone.
